ry explicit.","created_at":"2026-03-25T19:47:52Z"},{"id":1997,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-r4x01","author":"VioletSummit","text":"Validation result: telemetry verification succeeded end-to-end on worker vmi1227854, including artifact retrieval. Conformance verification on worker vmi1153651 compiled successfully but then failed during artifact retrieval with the same recursive .beads recovery overflow and rsync code 22. Conclusion: the defect persists, is worker-state-specific, and this repo can only document and pin excludes explicitly; the real fix belongs upstream in rch retrieval filtering and/or worker-path handling.","created_at":"2026-03-25T19:50:12Z"},{"id":1998,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-r4x01","author":"VioletSummit","text":"Repo-side follow-up: README now explicitly says that if rch reports remote command exit=0 and only then fails during artifact retrieval, agents should treat that as a tooling or worker-state problem rather than a Cargo failure, preserve the retrieval stderr, and retry on another worker or continue upstream investigation.","created_at":"2026-03-25T19:56:05Z"},{"id":1999,"issue_id":"flywheel_connectors-r4x01","author":"GentleOak","text":"Additional validation from GentleOak on 2026-03-25:
